<title>Autothrottle Disconnect Switches &ndash; Both Inoperative</title>
<dispcond category="C" downgrade="CATEGORY 2" maintenance="YES"
nbrins="2" nbrreq="0" operation="YES">
<remarks>
<para>May be inoperative provided:</para>
<numlist>
<numlitem><para>Autothrottles are not armed, and</para></numlitem>
<numlitem><para>Approach minimums do not require use of autothrottles.</para>
</numlitem>
</numlist>
<note><para>North Polar Route Restrictions.</para></note>
</remarks>
<operation key="UPS747MEL20070815102211">
<numlist>
<numlitem><para>If A/T ARM Switch is in the OFF position, the EEC
engine trim function will not operate. Small thrust asymmetry may
occur even if the throttles appear aligned.</para></numlitem>
<numlitem><para>#2 EICAS display of Thrust Management computations
are operative. </para></numlitem>
<numlitem><para>Set thrust manually.</para></numlitem>
</numlist>
</operation>
<limitation key="UPS747MEL20070815102212">
<numlist>
<numlitem><para>Downgrade Aircraft Category Dispatch Status to CAT
2.</para></numlitem>
<numlitem><para>North Polar Routes prohibited.</para></numlitem>
</numlist>
</limitation>
<placard>
<para>Placard near A/T Control switch "L (R) A/T DISC SW INOP" and
enter item in Aircraft Deferred Item Log.</para>
</placard>
<maintenance key="UPS747MEL20070815102213">
<numlist>
<numlitem><para>Set Autothrottle Arm Switch to OFF.</para></numlitem>
</numlist>
<para>Deferral of this item requires downgrading to the status indicated
in the A/C STATUS DISPATCH column below.</para>
